Vice President Biden met with Prime Minister Maris Kucinskis of Latvia to discuss various topics. The Vice President emphasized the US commitment to the security of the Baltic states and praised Latvia's efforts to strengthen its national defense. They also discussed expanding trade and investment ties between the US and Latvia. The Vice President congratulated Latvia on its accession to the OECD and encouraged the Prime Minister to continue implementing OECD recommendations, including reforming state-owned enterprises. The Vice President also urged further steps to improve Latvia's investment climate, including comprehensive reform to increase transparency, reduce corruption, and improve the efficiency of the judicial system.